  "title": "Cannot seem to get Mustache helpers working correctly",
  "body": "Taking from: http://mustache.github.io/mustache.5.html it should be possible to pass variable into the helpers however, it is not quite working for me.\n\nI have:\n\n``` javascript\n        instantsearch.widgets.hits({\n            container: '#resultHolder',\n            transformData: {\n                item: function(o){\n                    $.each(o.products, function(k, v){\n                        o.products[k] = {idx: k, obj: v};\n                    });\n                    return o;\n                }\n            },\n            templates: {\n                empty: 'No results',\n                item: '{{#products}}{{obj.id}}{{#helpers.button}}{{obj}}{{/helpers.button}}{{/products}}',\n            },\n            hitsPerPage: 20\n        })\n```\n\nnow `{{obj.id}}` works perfectly fine but `{{obj}}` just prints `{{obj}}` in this:\n\n``` javascript\n    search.templatesConfig.helpers.button = function(text){\n        console.log(text);\n    };\n```\n\nIt seems that maybe there is something missing here?\n",
